Key Match Events: Draymond Green had 13 points, eight rebounds and seven assists before a late ejection after two technical fouls in a 33-second span
Stephen Curry overcame a slow start to finish with 13 points, eight rebounds and five assists
Buddy Hield had 18 points and Moses Moody scored 14
Post-Match Reflections: Curry, who had scored 36 and 37 points the past two games, respectively, shot 4 for 9 with three 3-pointers
Lindy Waters III made his second start of the season, then fell to the floor after blocking a shot with 1:58 left in the second quarter due to a hyperextended left knee
Miscellaneous Highlights: A foul initially whistled against Green with 1:40 remaining before halftime when Jake LaRavia hit him in the face was challenged by the Warriors and the call was overturned. The foul was issued instead to LaRavia. Golden State won another challenge midway through the fourth
